caption: I used to work near by and loved to stop by and get my lunch there. The people working there make you feel like at home and the pasta is delicious 😋.  Great service and food.
Buffalo chicken roll is the best in the Slope and probably in Brooklyn.  Straight up! Its full of saucy chicken and cheese plus the bread in soft and holds everything in.
Great people. Absolutely delicious food.
Great food, nice service
Fabulous, fabulous food. Nice yard. Pleasant staff. Left happy!
Food was awesome
Always consistent. Clearly the best ingredients. More than a pizza place. The big name legacy pizza places in this neighborhood don't hold a candle tp Pizza+.
The service is always efficient, excellent vibes, very friendly employees. I will eat here again when I am in town.
Great food and staff
OK had to wait in line for food - it's was worth it!!! I was lucky to get a  MARGHERITA.
Very crowed! So I got take out.. So good! I'll will be back!
Terrific food, wonderful people! A neighborhood favorite!

Dependably delicious pizza - we've tried all different types and every one has been tasty and well-balanced. A favorite that everyone in the family can agree on. Oh, and it's staffed by wonderful people.
The server was very pleasant and they serve some whole wheat pizza
Yummmmmmmy

Not-so-old-school pizzeria with very good food, with table seating, outdoor garden or takeout.  They do not not sell slices after a certain time, but ordering a pie is never a bad option.  Soups, salads, calzones and dinners available.
If you have taste for classy New Yorker 🍕 pizza you are at the perfect place. Nice place.

I grew up with this place and am highly biased, but I will love them and there pizza for as long as they stand. I will say that I liked the old silverware much, much better. You can’t go wrong with their margherita pie.
Had the BBQ Pizza, so good! My wife and I just stopped by. So glad we did. We will be back!
Yum! Thanks for showing us Texans what NY pizza is all about. And I appreciated the GF vegan option so I could partake with my kids. Great service too!
Delicious pizza.

This place has been around since I was a little girl and it never disappoints. Being gluten free and vegan can make it difficult to find a really solid Brooklyn Pizza, but this place absolutely gets the job done. My husband isn't gluten free and usually doesn't like the food I eat but we were fighting over the last slice! Just make sure to ask for a lighter portion of vegan cheese if you're not a fan of the Daiya brand (which neither of us are for the most part, definitely not in heavy amounts). The crust was amazing, the toppings were fresh and the delivery was fast. I was born and raised in the area and now as a woman in my 30's if someone asked me where they should go to find the best vegan and gluten-free pizza I would tell them Pizza Plus. 😊  My husband got the eggplant parmesan and the salad was three leaves and a half tomato in addition to a small portion for a steep price. Still the best gluten free, vegan pizza in the area, it's just expensive as anything with smaller entrees.
Great food and amazing pizza!

Originally was headed to another place closer to where I was staying.  That place was closed on Monday, fortunately, because someone heard us say how disappointed we were because we were in the mood for pizza.  He recommended Pizza Plus and I am so glad he did.  Everything was superb, excellent service and exceptional pizza.  I am from out of state and this was one of the best I have ever had. You won't be disappointed

This pizza was AMAZING! We were in Brooklyn for 3 nights, and ate this for two of them, going out of our way to do so the second time. The cheese is perfect, not too much sauce, crisp crust, big beautiful pepperoni, and they even have a gluten-free pizza as an option! I highly recommend Pizza Plus.
Always a pleasant experience..I love the Broccoli and Linguine along with the homemade rolls
Great pizza and great staff.
another hidden gem in south slope. you can get vegan daiya cheese on anything. delivery is fast and they are very kind
The pizza is right on and the staff is super friendly!!!
Awesome pizza! Best I have had in a long time! Nice people!
Great food.   Great prices.  A neighborhood staple.

Daiya for the vegan cheese option--not too bad. Thin crust pizza, large is a huge pie. $30 is not justified for a two topping pizza though. Atmosphere was nice, seems family owned. Lots of sitting areas. Very busy!

Family and budget friendly. Pizza Plus has worked it's way in our family's rotation. I think one of my challenges with the place is the pizza is very inconsistent. The food is good and you get what you pay for (good portion for the price).
Vegan pepperoni pizza made for a great lunch.
Food was great

Really great tasting food! Calamari was crisp but not overdone, pizza toppings didn't compete with each other, crust was just right, but the service was best with a local and friendly vibe. Really nice surprise to find!
Great food! Fantastic service.

Although I've never stepped foot in the place, and I've only sampled two items from their extensive menu, I can honestly say that Pizza Plus makes some of the best pizza in NYC!  Here's how I know this: for at least six or seven years now, whenever i'm in the mood for pizza, I order a cheese pie from Pizza Plus. The order is always correct and arrives on time, and the pizza is always prepared exactly the same way (slightly well-done). The sauce is sweet without being overpowering, the cheese is fresh and the lightly browned crust is delicious enough to eat by itself.
The best! The pizza is delicious as is their entrees. Fast delivery service and every single person that works there or owns the place is wonderful and warm. Couldn't love it more.
17 years later still my favorite pizza place. If you want pizza on a Friday pick it up
Love this place! Pizzas are made fresh and the marinara sauce is amazing!
My family’s favorite restaurant!!! Hands down good food
Truly Family Oriented. Vegan Pie is Amazing

Can’t say enough good things about Pizza Plus. Though I have never been to the physical restaurant, their food is consistently yummy. Love their homemade buns that come with my orders. There is also genuine joy from the owner. She is always just so darn warn and inviting on the phone. Really nice to have that these days.
Cheap slices, ok pizza. Decent service.
Love the pasta

A fine local pizza spot. The ambiance isn’t exactly trendy or romantic, but it serves the family oriented clientele well. Pizza is good, tho it’s worth springing for the fresh mozz. Other dishes are mostly tasty staples, but salads are underwhelming. Friendly staff and owners are what make this place.
Love the food there staff there are really nice

Placed an order for delivery. Called after an hour and they told me it was a pick up order. However, the website had me add a tip. When I asked how long, they said another 40 minutes...which by that time my pizza would have sat out for two hours. Never again!
Excellent food. Old school spot
Great pizzas, loads of gluten free options and good service.
I love thos place. Have been gping nearly 20 years. My favorite pizza place in Brooklyn.
Always great

An old neighborhood favorite. Great pizza and pasta.
So delicious!
Awesome service. Their vegan pizza is absolutely delicious!
Wonderful pizza with friendly staff, and the option of vegan cheese!
Great food. Always friendly and pleasant.

I have gluten intolerance. Just earlier today I went to Pizza Plus, thinking that I would be delighted by their gluten free pizza. While it was pretty good for gluten free pizza, afterward I came home and had diarrhea and stomach bloating.  If I had to guess I’d say that it was cross contaminated, most likely by being cooked in the same oven as gluten pizza is.  Anyway I’m quite annoyed and angry that hey offer gluten free pizza, yet it’s not truely gluten free.

Cheesy delicious pizza and reasonable price! What bumped it up to 5 stars is that it was freshly made and they had kids coloring books and crayons available to keep the kids occupied while the pizza baked. Grateful for that because it would've been miserable waiting with them otherwise!
Love this place.

I wouldnt call it a traditional NY pizza spot, but it does have some nice Italian dishes. This place has more of a chic Italian eatery vibe. You can expect some great paninis with fresh ingredients The prices are a bit expensive but for quality ingredients I would say it's worth it. Food is made when ordered so expect to wait a bit for your food. I enjoyed this place and would go back.
Very friendly staff.Great taste .will come again :)
Solid menu of classic Brooklyn eats
excellent pizza place for kids
Nice cozy little place with decent food and good service
Great Food
Love this place!
Great place to eat at. Very clean establishment.
Great lunch specials. Full size pasta dish and a soda for under $10.

This place goes above and beyond customer service. I am always looking for a good pizza place to deliver, and not only is the pizza good but the service is excellent! Lara and Thomas helped me out big time!! You guys rock!!
Family owned & run. Besides pizza there are pasta plates, salads, sandwiches, specials, desserts, beer, & wine. Generous portions. Seasonal outdoor tables in back. Kid friendly. Delivery.
Love this place, my family has been coming here for 30+ years. Everyone who works there is super friendly. Great food, outdoor space in the warm months. Occasionally, there's a wait for a table.
There's only two pizzeria in Park slope and this is one of the original ones . Years of service to a great neighborhood.  Fast delivery and check out the lunch and kids menu special.  Thank you Roz .

Had dine-in pasta with my daughter. She had spaghetti and meatballs; I had penne with fried calamari. The food was good, and the service was great!  I especially liked the ample supply of crayons and coloring books and kids reading books, and Trivial Pursuit cards at the tables.

Nicest staff ever! I was accidentally charged three times and they called me to tell me and gave me my refund before I even knew it. Pizza was delivered so I can't attest to cleanliness of the place. GLUTEN FREE PIZZA is here and I am excited to have a local spot that will deliver!!! Pizza tasted OK- nothing like the real deal, but good when you are in a pinch.
I think the food is excellent and the prices are very reasonable for the location, Park Slope.

Great vegan pizza options!

Very good pizza and priced fairly. The service was excellent. The owners were extremely accommodating to our large group. We called with a group of over 20 people, and they set us up in there back yard. Very nice people!

There's a ricotta stuffed eggplant dish that is stupidly good. Great pizzas, pastas, everything fresh. Try shrimp and jalapeño pizza. Delivery has occasionally been a bit slow and slapdash but more often well-packaged and hot.

i grew up in park slope and had the luxury of being able to eat pizza plus's chicken parm regularly. it's been almost 10 years and I think about it at every restaurant and every time I eat homestyle Italian..  i have yet to eat a chicken parm that's better than yours. omg and your bread........ 🔥💥☄️🙌🎇🎆

Yhought it was a great place on first visit 2 weeks ago. Come in tonight to get dinner, ask for prosciutto on half the order to accommodate vegetarian; all or nothing according to rude presumably owner. Never Again. No wonder they were empty and 2 blocks away smiling pizzeria is packed to the gills!
Friendly staff, excellent atmosphere, abs very kid-friendly.

One of the best options for vegan pizza in NYC! They can make both pizza and calzones with vegan cheese (probably Daiya), and they use a generous amount.  The whole wheat dough is a nice option, they offer gluten free also. All these things cost extra, so it's not cheap. I like the vegan pizza here much better than Two Boots.
Excellent Calzone!
Family food fun.
The place to go for a chicken roll!!!!!
Not a bad slice. Good atmosphere.
This place is the best.The food is awesome and the pizza price is right.Very friendly,Clean,Helpful,I been coming here for a while now.I recommend this place to all..

The WORST pizza place ever. I ordered for delivery and it took over 2 hours to come and the pizza was cold.
Best pizza in Brooklyn!
Amazing service, beautiful pizza, overall wonderful experience
Roz is the BEST & their vegan pizzas are phenomenal. Also, best rolls ever!!
Great pizza & service

Had to get out of Manhattan for the day So were headed to the Prospect for the day but want to grab a quick lunch and happened upon Pizza Plus ( very pedestrian name for what turned out to be a great lunch/dinner spot) We had the Meatball hero and the Grilled Chicken with Roasted Peppers, Fresh Mozzarella with Pesto Panini (hubby and I always share so we can try both) and they were excellent!  Very flavorful meatballs in the hero with lots of melting mozzarella and the same for the panini. The service was very good, food was hot and portions just perfect. If I lived in the neighborhood this would be my go to spot.

The service was speedy, my waitress was incredibly friendly/gave me some great recommendations, and the salad was fantastic. Portions are insanely large and everything is reasonably priced, especially for a place in Park Slope.
Great pizza! Reasonable prices, lots of different options.
Solid delivery pizza.  Nothing amazing, but it works.
We used to go to this place all the time when we lived in the area. I love the grilled chicken pesto parm and still miss it.

A waste of $28. Got (2) bacon and sausage slices -- Tasted horrible. Their mozzarella sticks taste frozen bought and re-heated. Buffalo wings were soggy and lacked buffalo flavor; sure had the grease and color of buffalo, though. Will NEVER order from here again.

Good pizza. Super cheesy "veggie roll"(which can be customized to include meat) . Friendly service. Good prices. Caesar and pear+walnut salads didn't blow us away, but overall a really nice experience.
Delicious pizza!  The plain cheese was awesome.
Great pizza with lots of options. Tables can be hard to come by and I've never been when there aren't more than a few kids so if that's not your scene then look for something less family friendly.
Got a vegan pepperoni pizza - the best I have had since going vegan. It was amazing, really hit the spot.

Left this place without even ordering. The waitress threw the menus at us and seemed annoyed that we were asking so many questions. If you are coming here for the gluten free options then don't bother. A (small) gluten free pizza would cost you $14, plus $3 for vegan cheese (do people not understand that if you have celiac you probably can't have dairy either?) and $2 for every single topping. Disgraceful.

Amazing pizza. Get the Pesto Bianca - it's amazing! I believe we got a large last time and were shocked at the size of it. Very filling and there always seem to be leftovers. They have a lot of interesting pizza choices and even vegan options if you're into that. Unfortunately they don't sell single slices at night. If they did, I'd definitely stop by more on my way home from work!
Great fresh pizza. Well put together place even though it is a little small.

This is not just a pizza place it is an italian bistro restaurant. Maybe you wouldn't go here to spend big bucks but this is the place for a hearty meal in a nice casual atmosphere. The pizza is delicious, served up with any specifications you can think of as a full pie to the table. I like getting the whole wheat crust with extra spicy sauce and fresh mozzarella. Order a salad or vegetable with it and you have a meal. But when you look over at the couple next to you who got perfectly cooked al dente pasta in a delicious looking cream sauce or over broccoli rabe and chorizo you might regret not leaving room for an entree.
My favorite pizza in the neighborhood, and great value for money too

Pizza Plus is my favorite Brooklyn pizza joint, but I'm somewhat biased, since I'm mostly vegan.  Speaking with that in mind, their vegan pizzas, made with daiya (a convincing vegan cheese) are the best I've ever had.  As a plus, whole wheat crusts are also an option.  Best of all, walking inis always a warm, fun experience.
good pizzas with a sideline in relatively healthy options (excellent whole-wheat crust, good veggie pizza); and willing to deliver to the edge of prospect park on request!
